Prinring stuck on proccesing. Rebooting not working

check the CUPS web interface.  CUPS has a web server running on your system.  Open a browser and go to "localhost:631".  Check the job status, printer settings, etc.  Also check the error log at "/var/log/cups/error_log"
usually when a job is stuck it is because the printer is not available (bad connection or on another system that is turned off), or wrong driver.
